overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  seeking to validate its adherence to the provided Statement of Work and
  detailed questionnaire specification. The primary goal was to identify and
  implement any missing features. The assistant conducted a thorough review,
  generating a comprehensive plan that outlined several key areas for
  improvement. Subsequently, the assistant systematically implemented these
  features, including a critical 1-10 tiredness severity scale with safety
  messaging, advanced detection for COMISA and insufficient sleep syndrome, and
  the integration of valuable outbound resource links. Additionally, weighted
  scoring for EDS was introduced, the CSV export functionality was significantly
  expanded to include all questionnaire data, and new questions for pain and
  chronic fatigue screening were added. This structured approach ensured all
  identified gaps were addressed, enhancing the application's diagnostic
  capabilities and user guidance.
